OL,6,FThe cap, introduced in 2013 under the
OL,7,Fthen-Conservative and Liberal Democrat
OL,8,Fcoalition government as a way of
OL,9,F"restoring fairness to the welfare
OL,10,Fstate", sees the amount of benefits a
OL,11,Fhousehold receives reduced to ensure
OL,12,Fclaimants do not receive more than the
OL,13,Fcap limit.
OL,15,FThe two-child limit was first
OL,16,Fannounced in 2015 by the Conservatives
OL,17,Fand came into effect in 2017, and
OL,18,Frestricts child tax credit and
OL,19,Funiversal credit to the first two
OL,20,Fchildren in most households.
