OL,6,FIt comes as a separate report
OL,7,Fsuggested most people favour a
OL,8,Fsupportive approach over strict job-
OL,9,Fseeking rules for people on out-of-
OL,10,Fwork benefits.
OL,12,FThe polling, released by the New
OL,13,FEconomics Foundation (NEF), suggested
OL,14,Falmost two thirds (62%) of people
OL,15,Fquestioned felt job centres should
OL,16,Fprioritise offering a positive service
OL,17,Fto people who want support over
OL,18,Fenforcing sanctions against those who
OL,19,Fdo not follow the rules.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/15
