OL,6,FThe survey, of 2,041 UK adults in May,
OL,7,Falso found that almost 70% of people
OL,8,Fthought it was more important to
OL,9,Fsupport unemployed people into quality
OL,10,Fjobs than pushing them into any job as
OL,11,Fsoon as possible.
OL,13,FTom Pollard, head of social policy at
OL,14,Fthe NEF, said: "Politicians tend to
OL,15,Fassume that the public want the
OL,16,Fstrictest regime around out-of-work
OL,17,Fbenefits possible."
